Restore the stock Pythia 6.4.28 PDF dummy subroutine names. SND-LHC's
fork renamed PDFSET/STRUCTM/STRUCTP to *X variants for their internal
PDFLIB integration, but those symbols are what ROOT's EGPythia6 wrapper
and downstream consumers call into. Without this patch, linking against
libpythia6.so leaves undefined references to PDFSET/STRUCTM/STRUCTP at
consumer link time.

TODO: open upstream PR against SND-LHC/pythia6 so we can drop this patch.

--- a/pythia-6.4.28.f
+++ b/pythia-6.4.28.f
@@ -81353,7 +81353,7 @@ C*********************************************************************
 C...PDFSET
 C...Dummy routine, to be removed when PDFLIB is to be linked.

-      SUBROUTINE PDFSETX(PARM,VALUE)
+      SUBROUTINE PDFSET(PARM,VALUE)

 C...Double precision and integer declarations.
       IMPLICIT DOUBLE PRECISION(A-H, O-Z)
@@ -81385,7 +81385,7 @@ C*********************************************************************
 C...STRUCTM
 C...Dummy routine, to be removed when PDFLIB is to be linked.

-      SUBROUTINE STRUCTMX(XX,QQ,UPV,DNV,USEA,DSEA,STR,CHM,BOT,TOP,GLU)
+      SUBROUTINE STRUCTM(XX,QQ,UPV,DNV,USEA,DSEA,STR,CHM,BOT,TOP,GLU)

 C...Double precision and integer declarations.
       IMPLICIT DOUBLE PRECISION(A-H, O-Z)
@@ -81423,7 +81423,7 @@ C*********************************************************************
 C...STRUCTP
 C...Dummy routine, to be removed when PDFLIB is to be linked.

-      SUBROUTINE STRUCTPX(XX,QQ2,P2,IP2,UPV,DNV,USEA,DSEA,STR,CHM,
+      SUBROUTINE STRUCTP(XX,QQ2,P2,IP2,UPV,DNV,USEA,DSEA,STR,CHM,
      &BOT,TOP,GLU)

 C...Double precision and integer declarations.
